"Steve" == Steve Gardner <gardner@silas-1.cc.monash.edu.au> writes:

Steve> In fact, the Virus was one of the earliest examples of the
Steve> application of Pragmatic principles to Rule-design. It didn't
Steve> say "At the beginning of the week, a random Rule is amended in
Steve> such-and-such a way."; it said "Once each week, the Rulekeepor
Steve> selects a Rule at random and amends it in such-and-such a way."
Steve> And we never had any problems with the Virus.

I seem to recall that there were a few problems with the Virus, but
that they were not severe.  As I have previously noted, the incomplete
pragmatism of the Virus rule was such that a misapprehension as to the
number of Rules in the Ruleset would result in the Rulekeepor making
an erroneous Virus Report, possibly creating the mistaken impression
that a Rule had been infected as a result.  I am almost certain that
