####
Proto-Proposal
A Duty to Propose

[Comment: I've developed a procedure for dealing with Players who are On
Hold. I've tried to make the instructions to the Promotor as clear as I
can. Please bring any problems to my attention.]

Be it hereby resolved that a Rule, entitled "A Duty to Propose", be
created with the following text:

      Active Players not in their Grace Periods (henceforth in this
      Rule, 'Experienced Players') shall periodically incur a duty to
      submit a Proposal, as described in this Rule.

      The Promotor shall maintain an alphabetically sorted list of all
      Players. As soon as possible after the beginning of the Week, the
      Promotor shall perform the following procedure, which accomplishes
      the selection of the two Experienced Players to incur the duty to
      propose for that Week, the announcement of the names of those
      Players, and the updating of the list:

      (a) Experienced Players with an 'H' next to their names shall be
      selected before other Experienced Players. If there are more than
      two such Players, then the Promotor shall select the two highest
      on the list.
      
      (b) If, after selecting Experienced Players with an 'H' next to
      their names, there remain any places to be filled to bring the
      total number of Players selected for that Week to two, then the
      Promotor shall select the Experienced Player(s) highest on the list
      who do not have an asterisk ('*') next to their names. If there
      are not enough such Players, then only one Player is selected is
      selected for that Week.

      (c) The Promotor shall then announce in the Public Forum the names
      of the Players who have been selected for that Week. These Players
      have two weeks from the time of the Promotor's announcement to
      submit a Proposal. 

      (d) The Promotor shall then place an asterisk ('*') next to the
      names of the Players selected for that Week. If any of these
      Players had an 'H' next to their names, it shall be removed. 

      (e) If after step (d) is performed, it is the case that all
      Experienced Players have an asterisk next to their names, then the
      Promotor shall place an 'H' next to the name of any Player who is
      On Hold and who does not have an asterisk next to eir name, and
      remove all asterisks from the list.

      As stated above, the two Experienced Players selected by the
      Promotor each incur a duty to submit a Proposal within two weeks
      of the Promotor's announcement. Failure to do so is the Infraction
      of Failure to Propose, incurring a penalty of 1 Blot and 1 P-Note,
      to be detected and reported by the Promotor. The requirement to
      submit a Proposal placed upon a Player by this Rule lapses when
      the Player submits a Proposal, or when two weeks have elapsed from
      the time of the Promotor's announcement, whichever comes first.

####

It might be worth working an example thourgh to see how the above
procedure operates.

Initially, the list of Players will have the form: 

(A) (B) (C) (D) (E)

Let's say A is On Hold and C is a new Player, still in eir Grace Period.
Since neither A nor C are Experienced Players, according to the
definition, and since initially no Players have an 'H' next to their
names, the first Players to incur the duty to propose will be B and D.
After step (d), then, the list will look like this: 

(A) (B *) (C) (D *) (E)

In Week 2, A and C remain as before. So in step (b), there will not be
two Players to select. In this case, only E is selected for Week two.
After step (d), the list looks like this:

(A) (B *) (C) (D *) (E *)

Since it is now the case that every Experienced Player has an asterisk
next to their name, the condition in step (e) is met, and the list
becomes:

(A H) (B) (C) (D) (E)

In Week 3, A and C remain as before. As in Week 1, B and D are selected,
leaving us with:

(A H) (B *) (C) (D *) (E)

In Week 4, A comes Off Hold and C's Grace Period has concluded, while B
and E go On Hold. A and C are selected; after step (d) we have:

(A *) (B *) (C *) (D *) (E)

from which we can see that all Experienced Players once again have an
asterisk next to their names. After step (e), we have:

(A) (B) (C) (D) (E H)

Finally, in Week 5, E comes Off Hold, so A and E are selected, leaving
us with:

(A *) (B) (C) (D) (E *)

We can see that E did not succeed in avoiding eir turn by going On Hold
briefly. Also, the system picked up the fact that B had already had
their turn before going On Hold, and did not place an 'H' next to eir
name.

