This is a reminder to Players that on Mon, 12 Oct 12:03:24 GMT, R1859
(Secret Voting) will repeal itself, and the suppression clause will
delete itself from R1764 (Public Voting). At that moment, voting in the
Public Forum will cease to be illegal and resume being required (in the
sense that votes not sent to the PF will not be effective). Players
should adjust their behaviour accordingly.

It's probably also worth noting that all Active Players likely have a
duty to vote on one of P3794-3795. It's a little difficult to be certain
without an up-to-date Accountor's Report, but I do know that there are
plenty of VTs in circulation. According to the last Report (Sep 9), the
only Player too poor to vote would have been Blob, and he has received a
month's Salaries for two Offices since then.

